			tr
				td Visionaries (INFJ, INTJ)
					ul
						li Use models and show the overall framework of ideas
						li Focus on long-term planning and visions
						li Provide complex concepts and theories rather than facts and details
						li Use metaphors, symbols, and other figures of speech
						li Provide opportunities for them to question and seek new information
						li Show ways to change systems or improve processes
						li Relate experiences to theories and mental models
						li Use precise languages and watch out for multiple meanings of language
				td Assimilators (ISTJ, ISFJ)
					ul
						li Be detailed, accurate and precise
						li Focus on facts, real-life examples, and what is known
						li Make sure information is useful and relevant
						li Listen to their expertise and experience
						li Be practical; avoid abstraction, metaphors, and symbolism
						li Link what is new to what exists; integrate information with past experiences and knowledge
						li Provide step-by-step and structured explanations
						li Provide enough information for them to get a comprehensive understanding
						li Avoid surprises and ambiguity; provide detailed information as soon as possible
			tr
